I thought I&#039;d add my 2 cents.&lt;br /&gt;
&lt;br /&gt;
You can determine which foreign keys are disabled with this code:&lt;br /&gt;
&lt;br /&gt;
Select	object_name(parent_object_id) As TableName, &lt;br /&gt;
        name As ForeignKeyName &lt;br /&gt;
From	sys.foreign_keys&lt;br /&gt;
Where	is_ms_shipped = 0 and is_disabled = 1

